messages: Join our Discord for assistance, signing up for departments/civ orgs, and to communicate with other players - discord.gg/astrid
Make sure to use a snippet tool to create a mugshot of your character, and add it to your character by editing it, via (/characters).
To register a new vehicle, use the /vehicles command.
To become a community officer use the /community command.
Make sure to check (Settings -> Keybinds -> FiveM) to see all of the server keybinds, and to change them to your preference.
To view all of the available server commands, use the /cmds command.
To view your playtime use the /playtime command.
To file a bug report use the /bug command and fill out the form.
To report a player use the /report command.

additions: Player manager controlling ranks, playtime, metadata, etc.
Character manager controlling all of your characters data (name, dob, phone, metadata, backstory, job)
Client & Server callbacks for instant data retreval on the opposite, instead of using events, slowing down server performance and response time.
Connected player manager that controls automatic promoting to Honourable and high ping kicking and already connected logic.
Adaptive card on connecting with correct ban information formatting.
Job manager that handles going on duty, job blips (police, community police), automatic timesheet logging, updating callsign.
Vehicle manager than handles vehicle spawning permissions.
Weapon manager than handles weapon equiping permissions.
Ban manager that logs, saves and automatically processes bans, to automatically remove bans on the correct time.
Commend, kick & warning manager that logs and saves them.
Weather & time manager with real time syncing.
AOP manager that uses player count to determine the correct AOP for the server, unless a staff member disables and controls this manually.
Character vehicles manager which handles obtaining, creating, editing and deleting character vehicles.
Chat manager for running commands with permissions, chat types (Global instead of OOC, local & staff chat).
/me messages are drawn in the chat and above the players head for a set time.
Commends & warnings UI to view and search all of them via (/warnings | /commends).
Scoreboard that contains player server ID's, name and playtime, also shows players server ID above nearby peds.
Spawner UI that displays the server change-log, searchable keybinds (can be changed in your keybind settings), searchable commands and finally the rules.
Safezone manager to protects inside players from all forms of damage, from other players.

World manager that has a minimap controller (allowing you to zoom in & out of the minimap) and a variety of disablers & features such as (pickups, vehicle rewards, flashlight always on, disable idle cam, disable AI EMS & police, health re-charge disabled and interior ped cleaning, ambient sirens disabled, world traffic controlling).

Job manager with controllers (police & community police), going on duty, changing callsign, toggling the correct controllers based if you're on or off duty (recruitment menu, garage, unit blips, cuffing, grabbing).
Discord rich presence with cycling stages, buttons, image assets on hover information.
Staff manager and a variety of controllers such as the (staff menu, no clipping, gravity gun and ghost players after a player disconnects).

Vehicle manager with a massive amount of controllers (Speedzones for none staff & on duty LEO | Weapon prop inside vehicle | Anti rolling when upside down / Anti air control in a car | Leave LEO vehicle door open [Hold F] | Cruise control [F4] | Repair shops | GPS system that allows you to go to any street or postal [/gps street_name or /gps postal_code] | Keep wheel position when parked or exiting /turning off vehicle | Vehicle rolling via interactive eye | Seatbelt toggling, ejecting and damage if toggled, based on your speed | Seating inside a vehicle (can be done via the F3 hex menu) | Seat shuffling with /shuffle when in the passenger seat | Drive-by controlling [allows you to fire in any seat if driving less than 30 mph, if you're exceeding 30mph and you're the driver, you won't be able to fire your weapon]).

Weapon manager with a massive amount of controllers (Disarming (you get disarmed if you're shot in the hand, you will drop your weapon on the ground) | Reloading [R] | Firing modes & weapon safety | Spam preventor (restricts all semi automatic weapons to require you to re-press the firing key, preventing you from holding it down, to continuously fire the weapon) | Recoil | Disablers (Disables you from combat rolling, spam punching & doing the silly combat stance after firing a weapon) | Jamming [G] | Taser cartridges & laser [K] | Weapons on back).
Menu manager with menu & submenu classes.
Progress class with real time UI, callbacks based on behaviour (start, cancelling, finishing).
Notification class with a variety of custom options and types.
Poly & Box zone helpers rewritten in TypeScript for the core.

Player names that display your server ID, character name, job department and rank, there are also a variety of icons based on what you're doing (typing, talking, driver, passenger, in a car, in a bike, health), different coloured name based on your rank in the server, staff members can see players steam names and their rank.
Death system with custom animations for attachment support, reviving and respawn menu after certain amount of time, respawn counter and input key UI.
World blip controllers for a variety of world locations (shops, police & fire/ems stations, interiors & activities for civilians).
Bug reporting controller that can be done via the /bug command, which will open a bug report UI form, for you to fill out.
Hex interactive menu that can be toggled via [F3], of course like every other keybind, this can be changed in your (Settings -> Keybinds -> FiveM).
Player & Vehicle HUD controller that can be toggled with [Right CTRL].

Variety of civilian controllers (Carrying (places a player over your shoulder), Gagging (sock in players mouth, disables them talking), kidnapping (places a bag prop over a players head and turns their screen black), surrending (placing hands up/down, kneeling on the ground).
Radio that allows you to use either your mouse, or your arrow keys to control the radio, you also have the ability to set 3 custom radio on & off clicks.
DP Emotes.
Radar for emergency vehicles that allows you to set fastest speed, track vehicle plates, etc.
Loading screen with spawning in log and progress bar, also contains your steam avatar, your rank, steam name and server rank.
LVC lighting system for emergency vehicles (that has unique sirens for each department, and for some of the sub divisions of that dept).
Nozzle refueling system.

A variety of server assets (Addon Vehicles, EUP, Weapons, Sirens, Pause & Minimap, Engine Sounds, Coloured HUD, nitrous (orange -> purple), replacement weapons and all of the DLC clothing (Diamond Casino, Cayo Perico, The Contract), you should also be able to fly to the Cayo Perico island.

rules.title: Age Requirement
rules.description: Players must be 13 years of age to play in order to comply with Discord ToS.

rules.title: Microphones
rules.description: Although are required do not have to be used at all times depending on RP scenarios. Use of /me is required when the roleplay props such a response. Use of any homophobic, racist, overly sexual or derogatory remarks out of character is prohibited. Screaming and/or spamming music loudly to hinder people from hearing is not allowed.

rules.title: Trolling/Griefing
rules.description: Trolling/Griefing is the act of intentionally angering or irritating another player with malicious intent and will not be tolerated. This does include mistreatment and harassment directed at law enforcement out of RP. Some examples would include consistently stalking a player to force RP. Screaming at police or mic spamming while trying to tell them how to do their job while out of character. Due to the majority of our LEO personel not actually being LEOs in real life, we will not tolerate excessive abuse, antagonizing, or badgering out of RP. However we are open to constructive criticism and as long as you follow the chain of command, comments and/or the correct procedures you know and make us aware of can be added to the LEO SOP, however this criticism should not be done in game or cause you to break character.

rules.title: Metagaming
rules.description: Metagaming will not be tolerated. This includes using information gained outside of roleplay. Including but not limited to: Stream Sniping/Stalking, conversations outside of server Discord Voice and Chat Channels Flagged as In-Character, may have its contents used within roleplay. Using outside information gathered from other methods besides in server roleplaying & investigation is not permitted. Stream Sniping or Stream Stalking is not permitted. Conversations outside of the server are permitted and encouraged but do not use the information from these conversations in the server. Staff specifically are not allowed to utilize administrative tools to gain insider information into another player; this includes but not limited to 'Spectating', ''Reverse Plate'; or 'Garage View' of any player for reasons outside of your administrative role. Use of this information for anything within the confines of RolePlay is strictly prohibited & may result in removal from Community Staff.

rules.title: Power Gaming, Exploiting, and Modding
rules.description: Power Gaming, Exploiting, and Modding will not be tolerated. Using either game or roleplay mechanics to alter a situation to maximize a player's positive outcome is not allowed. If a bug or exploit is discovered it is up to the player to report this via a ticket on the website. Modding is prohibited. SQL or Menu Injections are strictly prohibited. If a bug or exploit is discovered by you and you fail to report it, if it is discovered by administration, you risk your position in the community.

rules.title: AFK-Away from Keyboard
rules.description: Do not go AFK or idle via Alt-Tab or leave your game minimized for long periods of time. If you must leave your keyboard, attempt to move your character to a secluded location in which the likelihood of your character crossing paths with another RolePlayer are minimal. (Example: Zancudo Boat Ramp)

rules.title: RDM - Random Death Match
rules.description: RDM will not be tolerated. An interaction with a player must be established before you can kill someone. A valid in-character exchange or an established chain of events leading to a violent action. Police will react to a threat at least one level above the current show of force. However, if an officer feels their life is in danger they will use deadly force.

rules.title: VDM - Random Vehicle Deathmatch
rules.description: VDM will not be tolerated. Randomly running over others is not acceptable. You can run someone over if they pose a threat or you have a sufficient character reason to do so. Police may at times when unable to stop a subject, who is running on foot, use a police car to bump said subject to stop them.

rules.title: Breaking Character
rules.description: Breaking Character will not be tolerated. You must not break character unless spoken to by staff. There are no exceptions. If you do not remain in character when speaking with Law Enforcement Officers, Firemen, and Medics they will have a staff member handle the situation and terminate the RP Scene allowing that Emergency Services person to get back on duty.

rules.title: LTAP
rules.description: Leaving To Avoid Punishment will not be tolerated. This is the act of quitting or disconnecting from the Server to avoid receiving punishment from the Staff Team.

rules.title: Combat Logging
rules.description: The intentional leaving of the server to avoid roleplay consequences for your actions.

rules.title: NITRP (No Intent to Roleplay)
rules.description: While being in the FiveM server, not conducting any roleplay scenarios - causing issues - and all around disruptiveness to others.

rules.title: Staff Impersonation
rules.description: Pretending to be an Astrid Network Staff Team member when actually not one. Anyone without staff tags in Discord is not a staff member.

rules.title: Repairing/Healing Yourself and Vehicles while in a Scenario
rules.description: While in progression of a roleplay scene, repairing your vehicle and/or healing yourself in an unrealistic/not legit manner.

rules.title: Injecting into RP
rules.description: Joining scenarios that are in-progress, that you were not explicitly originally involved in is against the rules.

rules.title: Player Death
rules.description: Only YOU the player may decide if your character is DEAD in RP. Just because someone claims they have shot you in the head 20 times and therefore you must be dead does not mean you have to. The charge of murder can only be given when a characters actions have caused another player to decide it has killed their character. Players that decide their character has died MUST change from said character for their next RP scene/situation and should not use any information gathered on the day of their murder from the previous character's life span towards any future roleplay involving revenge.

rules.title: Chat
rules.description: Chat is to be used for In-Character purposes as much as possible. Using chat in a disrespectful manner may result in disciplinary action. Do not get into drawn out arguments in chat, if you are unhappy with a person, ask them to come speak to you in Discord or make a complaint Ticket on the website.

rules.title: RP it First, Report it later
rules.description: When in an RP scenario, completely finish the RP scene before attempting to deal with it as a staff situation or reporting it to staff. Engagement with staff, if done quickly, can be handled in game but should be done in a secluded area away from any on-going RP. If the situation entails disrupting RP for a period longer than 15 minutes, the situation should be handled in Discord. If for any reason the FailRP is excessive, you may dis-engage from the scene and report it to an admin/mod as you feel necessary and go back as on-duty.

rules.title: Realistic Driving
rules.description: Driving realistic in the AOP will be enforced at all times. All traffic control devices should be honored as such however RED LIGHTS are treated as STOP SIGNS, requiring the FULL STOP of your vehicle before proceeding. It is highly encouraged to not be driving off road unless in a realistic form with a vehicle capable of handling it.

rules.title: Value your RP LIfe
rules.description: At all times you must value your life and the life of others. If you're at a clear disadvantage, comply with the attackers demands as you would in real life.

rules.title: Kidnapping
rules.description: To kidnap any player (this includes the police), there must be at least 6 officers on-duty. If you are unsure on how many cops are on duty, refer to the scoreboard. If the number of on duty police fall below the requirement you may continue to RP however attempt to speed up the timeline of completion to avoid utilizing all on-duty officers for your one scene. Kidnappings must be for a very good roleplay reason. Any kidnapping must make the situation more enjoyable. Nobody wants to be locked in silence whilst taken hostage for long periods of time. Medics cannot be kidnapped or killed.

rules.title: Terrorism and Suicide Roleplay
rules.description: Any roleplay that is or may be concerted terrorism is not acceptable under any circumstance. This does include any type of suicide roleplay as it goes against the Value your Life Rule.

rules.title: Getting Revived by EMS
rules.description: When engaged with Medical Staff it is up to the player to respond in chat where required to notify the Medical Personal of the status of your character; (ie Dead, Unconscious, Bleeding, etc). When revived in game by Medical Personnel per your health status indicated in chat, you will be REQUIRED to adhere to the directions of medical personnel regarding whether or not you will need to be transported to hospital for further attention, or if you are free to go at the scene. Example#1: You passed out due to not eating or drinking, the EMS may release you on scene. Example#2: You in game killed due to gunshot wounds, you will be transported to the hospital or nearest medical facility for additional attention. When you are medically revived, youre in medical custody until a member of EMS releases you (this also includes if you are revived by Police). For this reason, once revived by a medic or police officer, you may not simply run off or jump up and instantly start shooting at the police again. You were downed and you lost the fight and its unrealistic to recover that quickly.

rules.title: Nudity
rules.description: Character models with nudity are permitted within a situational roleplay scene

rules.title: Gangs and Drugs
rules.description: At this current time no policy is in place, however, if an issue arises that requires addressing the Management team and staff will address it when necessary. All server rules are expected to be followed when roleplaying or using any of these mechanics. No Territory or Turfs can be claimed or occupied where populated RP occurs. Territories are limited to residential sections of the map, and NOT any large sections that are densely populated. Gangs are not allowed to be in constant battle or DM with another gang involving police / other players.

rules.title: New Life Rule
rules.description: You can return with another character but may not get involved or have knowledge of the previous life. If the situation moves location and you accidentally get caught up in it you must make every effort to leave. If a situation leaves all police dead, they will revive, and return to patrol like nothing happened. Police will be expected to not remember the scene.

rules.title: Reasonable Character Name
rules.description: While names that are clever are allowed. Names that are offensive or vulgar are not permitted. Names that Management deem are unacceptable will be changed immediately.

rules.title: Unrealistic Phone Use
rules.description: Using a phone while in cuffs or in Police custody/Prison is considered failRP - this includes sending messages and tweeting.

rules.title: Cop Baiting
rules.description: Do not purposefully try and get police attention on you by doing things you would not do with an officer near you. Attempting to gather the attention of law enforcement by committing infractions in front of police with desire to trigger a police pursuit or encounter (Commonly known as 'Police Baiting' or 'Cop Baiting'). Burnouts, or Peeling of tires (outside the normal GTA burn out of cars at take off). Hitting, Colliding, Cutting Off, Passing Aggressively, FishTailing, Spinning Out, Ramming another car or player in front of police. This includes but is not limited to; burning out in the middle of intersections, purposefully revving your motor at lights to bait a pullover/chase, purposely committing traffic violations in the vicinity of a police officer. Police Officers will have the final say in determining whether what you are doing is considered cop baiting or not. If they decide that your actions are considered cop baiting they may ignore you all together and continue to patrol as if you are not there. If they decide that you are not cop baiting, they will attempt to RP with you. No conversations should happen out of RP to discuss whether cop baiting is taking place or not.

rules.title: Police Stations, Fire Stations, Hospitals
rules.description: Entering the detention area, roof, offices, locker, the back of Mission Row or any Police Station is strictly prohibited unless it is directly related to the roleplay situation that has been in play for at least 5 minutes and the location has changed to one of these official government locations. Otherwise only police and invited guests are permitted.

rules.title: Unrealistic Character Roles
rules.description: Being a CEO who is a Lawyer who is a Mechanic who is a Gangster is not what we expect. Pick what style suits your character and stick to it. Example, if you are a hobo, we expect you to be doing hobo activities and not representing someone as a lawyer. With the multi character option, you can create characters who are these different roles but try to build and focus on a select few.

rules.title: Building Into Crime
rules.description: Criminal activities can be fun, however do not join the server expecting to commit the serious criminal activities such as robbing the bank from the beginning. Build a reputation of crime over time. You should attempt to make connections by making friends and working your way into more serious crime.

rules.title: Wanted Level
rules.description: Criminals should be mindful of the attention from police their actions may generate. Give time between your crimes for things to cool down. You should expect to get more police attention, longer jail time/fines, and investigations if you repeatedly commit crimes in a small time frame.

rules.title: In-Game Issues
rules.description: If you have any issues about a situation wait until its over to talk it out, don't ruin situations because something wrong may have occurred. Staff Members will try not to interrupt situations they may intervene if the situation has irreversible effects. If you want to dispute a player contact a member of the staff team after the scenario.

rules.title: Aim To Keep Crime Hidden
rules.description: As this is an active first world state you should be aiming to keep all crime underground. Continuously broadcasting activities in public are going to create lots of police attention and your time as a criminal will be short-lived.

rules.title: Mass Murderer
rules.description: If a player decides to make a mass murderer and go on a spree the player should expect this type of character to be short-lived and once caught to be punished to the fullest extent of the law. You may be asked to switch your character and make a new one.

rules.title: Roleplay Standards:
rules.description: We as a Community will strive to make sure that all RP Scenarios are enjoyable for everyone involved. To accomplish this, we must understand that we can't simply have it our way every time when it comes to our own RP Scenarios. Cops are not always going to catch the bad guy/guys. Criminals are not always going to get away scotch free. Even though winning (the scenario ending exactly as you wanted it to) can be enjoyable we must understand that the scenario will often favor the side (Cops vs. Criminals) that works best as a team and communicates and plans. We also understand that each person's skill level is different when it comes to RP. For this reason we ask that everyone be tolerant and understanding when RP'ing with players with less experience than themselves.
